最优套保比率（风险最小化的套保比率）¶

1n

$\Delta \Pi = n\Delta G- \Delta H$

()$\frac{\partial \Delta \Pi}{\partial \Delta H} = \frac{\partial (n\Delta G- \Delta H)}{\partial \Delta H} = n \frac{\partial \Delta G}{\partial \Delta H} -1 = 0$ $n = \frac{\partial \Delta H}{\partial \Delta G}$

$r_{H} = \frac{H_{1}-H_{0}}{H_{0}} = \frac{\Delta H}{H_{0}},r_{G} = \frac{\Delta G}{G_{0}}$,

$n = \frac{\partial \Delta H}{\partial \Delta G} = \frac{H_{0}* \partial r_{H}}{G_{0}* \partial r_{G}}$

nNn,N

$N = n*\frac{Q_{H}}{Q_{G}} = \frac{\partial (\Delta H)*Q_{H}}{\partial (\Delta G)*Q_{G}} = \frac{Q_{H}*H_{0}* \partial r_{H}}{Q_{G}*G_{0}* \partial r_{G}}$

$\sigma_{\Pi}^{2}$

$\frac{\partial^{2} (\sigma_{\Pi}^{2})}{\partial n^{2}} = 2\sigma_{G}^{2}>0$$\sigma_{\Pi}^{2}$n$n = \frac{\sigma_{HG}^{2}}{\sigma_{G}^{2}}$

    $y = \frac{\tilde{W}_{T}-\tilde{W}_{t}}{ \sqrt{T-t}} $,$ d_{2} = \frac{ln(\frac{S_{t}}{K}+(r-\sigma^{2}))}{\sigma \sqrt{T-t}} $,$d_{1} = d_{2}+\sigma\sqrt{T-t} = \frac{ln(\frac{S_{t}}{K}+(r+\sigma^{2}))}{\sigma \sqrt{T-t}}$

  7. \begin{aligned} E_{Q}(X_{T}|\Bbb{F}_{t})&= \int_{-d_{2}}^{+\infty} S_{t} * e^{(r-\frac{1}{2}\sigma^{2}) * (T-t)+\sigma*\sqrt{T-t}*y} *\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} *e^{-\frac{y^{2}}{2}} dy - \int_{-d_{2}}^{+\infty} K *\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} *e^{-\frac{y^{2}}{2}} dy\\ & = S_{t}* e^{r(T-t)} * \int_{-d_{2}}^{+\infty} \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}* e^{-\frac{y^{2}}{2}+\sigma* \sqrt{T-t}*y-\frac{1}{2} *\sigma^{2}} dy -K *\Phi(d_2) \\ &=S_{t}* e^{r(T-t)} * \int_{-d_{2}-\sigma*\sqrt{T-t}}^{+\infty} \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}* e^{-\frac{y^{2}}{2}+\sigma* \sqrt{T-t}*y-\frac{1}{2} *\sigma^{2}}d(y+ \sigma *\sqrt{T-t})-K *\Phi(d_2)\\ &= S_{t}* e^{r(T-t)} \Phi(d_1) - K *\Phi(d_2) \end{aligned}

  8. $$c^{E}_{t} = S_{t}* \Phi(d_1) - K*e^{-r(T-t)} *\Phi(d_2) $$
    • $\Phi(X)$(CDF)

复制策略¶
    • $\Phi(d_1) = \frac{\partial V}{\partial S}$,$\Pi$$S_t*\Phi(d_1)$
    • $K*e^{-r(T-t)}\Phi(d_2)$
  • $\frac{\partial V}{\partial S} = \Phi(d_{1})$:
    • $ V_{t} =S_{t}* \Phi(d_1) - K*e^{-r(T-t)} *\Phi(d_2) $
    • \begin{aligned} \frac{\partial V}{\partial S} &= \frac{\partial S* \Phi(d_1)- K*e^{-r(T-t)} *\Phi(d_2)}{\partial S} \\ &= \Phi(d_1) + S*\phi(d_1) * \frac{\partial (d_1)}{\partial S} - K*e^{-r(T-t)} *\phi(d_2) * \frac{\partial (d_2)}{\partial S} \\ &= \Phi(d_1) \end{aligned}
    • $ S*\phi(d_1)= K*e^{-r(T-t)} *\phi(d_2)$,$ \frac{\partial (d_1)}{\partial S} = \frac{\partial (d_2)}{\partial S} $
